<title id="477">Conref concept: HP Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade System / Hardware Requirements</title>
<rcbody>
        <shortdesc id="shortdesc" id="2">For successful software installation and operation, the Titanium
            Server hardware platform must meet specific requirements.</shortdesc>
        <prolog id="prolog_N10017_N1000E_N10001">
            <author id="170">Jim Owens</author>
            <author id="3">Pedro Sanchez</author>
        </prolog>
        <conbody id="conbody_N10026_N1000E_N10001">
            <p id="SysEngGuidelines_reference" id="468">For detailed configuration information, refer to the <cite id="469">HP Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade System Engineering Guidelines</cite>.</p>
            <section id="section_N10036_N1002E_N10001" id="452">
                <title id="453">System Architecture</title>
                <p id="454">The HP Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade consists of a set of hosts connected to
                    internal and external networks, as illustrated in the following figure.</p>
                <!-- note id="note_N10087_N10036_N10027_N1000F_N10001" id="489">
                    <p id="490">For a minimal two-server configuration, the controller and
                        compute functions are combined on a single host.</p>
                </note -->
                <fig id="fig-logical-architecture" id="5">
                    <title id="6">HP Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade Reference Logical Architecture</title>
                    <image href="jow1404333560781.image" id="image_c1k_wtk_cn" id="7" width="6in">
                        <alt id="455">HP Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade logical view</alt>
                    </image>
                </fig>
                <p id="460">This figure is simplified to show internal network connections to
                    just one host of each type.</p>
                <ul id="ul_z11_czg_vp">
                    <li id="470">
                        <p id="471">Two controller nodes are required.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li id="472">
                        <p id="473">For systems using storage nodes, two storage nodes are
                            required.</p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p id="336">The HP Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade runs on all x86-64 processors that support
                    Intel Virtualization Technology (VT) VT-x/VT-d extensions. However, the Titanium
                    Server's kernel has been optimized specifically for the Intel Xeon-core family
                    of processors.</p>
            </section>
